#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:7
msgid "Video Output Overlay Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:9
msgid "**Also known as On-Screen Display (OSD)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:11
msgid ""
"Some video output devices can overlay a framebuffer image onto the outgoing "
"video signal. Applications can set up such an overlay using this interface, "
"which borrows structures and ioctls of the :ref:`Video Overlay <overlay>` "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:16
msgid ""
"The OSD function is accessible through the same character special file as "
"the :ref:`Video Output <capture>` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:21
msgid ""
"The default function of such a ``/dev/video`` device is video capturing or "
"output. The OSD function is only available after calling the :ref:"
"`VIDIOC_S_FMT <VIDIOC_G_FMT>` ioctl."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:27
msgid "Querying Capabilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:29
msgid ""
"Devices supporting the *Video Output Overlay* interface set the "
"``V4L2_CAP_VIDEO_OUTPUT_OVERLAY`` flag in the ``capabilities`` field of "
"struct :c:type:`v4l2_capability` returned by the :ref:`VIDIOC_QUERYCAP` "
"ioctl."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:36
msgid "Framebuffer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:38
msgid ""
"Contrary to the *Video Overlay* interface the framebuffer is normally "
"implemented on the TV card and not the graphics card. On Linux it is "
"accessible as a framebuffer device (``/dev/fbN``). Given a V4L2 device, "
"applications can find the corresponding framebuffer device by calling the :"
"ref:`VIDIOC_G_FBUF <VIDIOC_G_FBUF>` ioctl. It returns, amongst other "
"information, the physical address of the framebuffer in the ``base`` field "
"of struct :c:type:`v4l2_framebuffer`. The framebuffer device ioctl "
"``FBIOGET_FSCREENINFO`` returns the same address in the ``smem_start`` field "
"of struct :c:type:`fb_fix_screeninfo`. The ``FBIOGET_FSCREENINFO`` ioctl and "
"struct :c:type:`fb_fix_screeninfo` are defined in the ``linux/fb.h`` header "
"file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:51
msgid ""
"The width and height of the framebuffer depends on the current video "
"standard. A V4L2 driver may reject attempts to change the video standard (or "
"any other ioctl which would imply a framebuffer size change) with an "
"``EBUSY`` error code until all applications closed the framebuffer device."
msgstr ""

