#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:107
msgid "Overlay Window and Scaling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:109
msgid ""
"The overlay is controlled by source and target rectangles. The source "
"rectangle selects a subsection of the framebuffer image to be overlaid, the "
"target rectangle an area in the outgoing video signal where the image will "
"appear. Drivers may or may not support scaling, and arbitrary sizes and "
"positions of these rectangles. Further drivers may support any (or none) of "
"the clipping/blending methods defined for the :ref:`Video Overlay <overlay>` "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:117
msgid ""
"A struct :c:type:`v4l2_window` defines the size of the source rectangle, its "
"position in the framebuffer and the clipping/blending method to be used for "
"the overlay. To get the current parameters applications set the ``type`` "
"field of a struct :c:type:`v4l2_format` to "
"``V4L2_BUF_TYPE_VIDEO_OUTPUT_OVERLAY`` and call the :ref:`VIDIOC_G_FMT "
"<VIDIOC_G_FMT>` ioctl. The driver fills the struct :c:type:`v4l2_window` "
"substructure named ``win``. It is not possible to retrieve a previously "
"programmed clipping list or bitmap."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:127
msgid ""
"To program the source rectangle applications set the ``type`` field of a "
"struct :c:type:`v4l2_format` to ``V4L2_BUF_TYPE_VIDEO_OUTPUT_OVERLAY``, "
"initialize the ``win`` substructure and call the :ref:`VIDIOC_S_FMT "
"<VIDIOC_G_FMT>` ioctl. The driver adjusts the parameters against hardware "
"limits and returns the actual parameters as :ref:`VIDIOC_G_FMT "
"<VIDIOC_G_FMT>` does. Like :ref:`VIDIOC_S_FMT <VIDIOC_G_FMT>`, the :ref:"
"`VIDIOC_TRY_FMT <VIDIOC_G_FMT>` ioctl can be used to learn about driver "
"capabilities without actually changing driver state. Unlike :ref:"
"`VIDIOC_S_FMT <VIDIOC_G_FMT>` this also works after the overlay has been "
"enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:137
msgid ""
"A struct :c:type:`v4l2_crop` defines the size and position of the target "
"rectangle. The scaling factor of the overlay is implied by the width and "
"height given in struct :c:type:`v4l2_window` and struct :c:type:`v4l2_crop`. "
"The cropping API applies to *Video Output* and *Video Output Overlay* "
"devices in the same way as to *Video Capture* and *Video Overlay* devices, "
"merely reversing the direction of the data flow. For more information see :"
"ref:`crop`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:147
msgid "Enabling Overlay"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-osd.rst:149
msgid ""
"There is no V4L2 ioctl to enable or disable the overlay, however the "
"framebuffer interface of the driver may support the ``FBIOBLANK`` ioctl."
msgstr ""
